*** Spiritual Hand part II ***
.
📍Setif- Algeria 🇩🇿
.
*Story:
Hands learn more than minds do, hands learn how to hold other hands, how to grip pencils and mold poetry, how to tickle pianos and dribble a basketball and grip the handles of a bicycle how to hold old people, and touch babies. I love hands like I love people, they’re the maps and compasses in which we navigate our way through life, some people read palms to tell your future, but I read hands to tell your past, each scar marks the story worth telling, each calloused palm, each cracked knuckle is a missed punch or years in a factory. Now I’ve seen Middle Eastern hands clenched in Middle Eastern fists pounding against each other like war drums.
.
